text: following on from generating login
logout reports we will now walk through
how to create scheduled reports
this can be important when you want to
schedule this report creation on a
periodic basis and share with your
organization
you can schedule reports either from
Saved reports or once you create the
report
first I will show you how to share the
report from Saved reports
under analytics and optimization
choose saved reports
under login logout report
hover the mouse pointer over the row
containing the name of the report to
schedule
and choose the schedule report icon
toggle on published report to the
organization scheduling a report
requires that it be published to your
organization
on the scheduled report page under
recurrence for Generate this report
you can choose whether to generate the
report daily or weekly
let's select weekly
select the day or days of week on which
to run the report
let's select Monday
choose the time zone
let's select U.S Central
you can add prefix to the S3 path to the
saved report you can use prefixes to
organize the data that you store in
Amazon S3 buckets a prefix is a string
of characters at the beginning of object
key name
so choose delivery options and enter a
value in the prefix field
the prefix is added to the path between
reports and the report name for example
my prefix
choose create
if you have a requirement to delete a
report then you can hover over the row
for the report to delete
and choose delete icon choose delete
again
thank you for joining me in learning how
to create schedule login logout report
